plus    TLA+ code follows. Please note that the actual implementation may vary based on specific requirements and constraints of your system or project, so this is a general guideline you can use as reference when writing out tests cases etc.:    # Constants & Invarients (TypeOK)
CONSTANTS  NATURALS  = 0..MAXNAT;     INVARIANTS ZSEQUENCES = {ZIndices, LEXORDER};            TLC CONFIG: SPECIFICATION={INITIALSTATE : StateInitValue}, EMPTY_TRANSACTION = <<>>
# Operators on finite zero-indexed sequences (TLA+) – Definitions for ZSequences module.   # Define operators to work with sets of elements in a sequence, where the set is defined by its length n and consists only from numbers between {0..n}.       OPERATOR SEQUENCE(s), INV s = (ZIndices)(LEXORDER)
